    if(len(DEVICE_TYPE_DATA['DEVICE_TYPE'][i])==2):
        DEVICE_TYPE_DATA['DEVICE_TYPE'][i]='FM'

            DEVICE_TYPE_DATA['DEVICE_TYPE'][i]='F'

            DEVICE_TYPE_DATA['DEVICE_TYPE'][i]='M'

# Handling the Outliers

Purchase_Journey_num=Purchase_Journey[['Duration','MobilePanel','FixedPanel']]

def outlier_capping(x):
    ul = x.quantile(0.75)+1.5*(x.quantile(0.75)-x.quantile(0.25))
    ll = x.quantile(0.25)-1.5*(x.quantile(0.75)-x.quantile(0.25))
    x = x.clip_upper(ul)
    x = x.clip_lower(ll)
    return x

Purchase_Journey[['Duration','MobilePanel','FixedPanel']]=Purchase_Journey[['Duration','MobilePanel','FixedPanel']].apply(lambda x: outlier_capping(x))

def normalize(column):
    upper = column.max()
    lower = column.min()
    y = (column - lower)/(upper-lower)
    return y
